**Install Softwares from Debian Repository**
<text>

to install softwares like firefox , vlc
	only root user can install/update softwares
	command 'su' is use to switch to root

</text>
```bash
su
```
<text>

after that
update sources repository database

</text>
```bash
apt update
```
<text>
then to install software use command
"apt install [package_name]"

for </text>
`Chrome`
<text>

</text>
```bash
apt install chromium
```
<text>
for </text>
`VLC`
<text>

</text>
```bash
apt install vlc
```

<text>
for </text>
`Firefox`
<text>

</text>
```bash
apt install firefox-esr
```
