</text>

**Install Software from outside**

<text>
 
first search on internet like 
example : "how to install vlc on debian"
remember our OS is 
✅ arm64 = aarch64 = arm 64bit 
 ---  not ---
❌ x86 = i386 = 32bit 
❌ x86_64 = amd64 = 64bit 


installing softwares from external sources 
example : 

</text>
`Visual Code Studio`
<text>

dowload Visual code in .deb arm64 </text>

<link view="inline" name="Link" url="https://code.visualstudio.com/#alt-downloads" >

<text>

</text>

<img src="shots/vscode_select.jpg" width="300" >

<text>

then login to root user by command 'su'
then navigate to downloaded folder and run

</text>
```bash
cd ~/Downloads
apt install ./code_*.deb
```
<text>

run command "code --no-sandbox" in GUI terminal as user
to start visual code

</text>
```bash
code --no-sandbox
```
<text>

all done


</text>




